      "side": 1,
      "message": "What if A and B both have nested type C, then C\u0027s constructor is duplicated in A and B. Is it worth keeping a struct similar to typeRegistry in which you deduplicate constructor functions?",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 60,
        "startChar": 3,
        "endLine": 60,
        "endChar": 63
      },
      "revId": "0967c54840d687a04c598f4296a8ba141ac41741",
